&gt; &lt;OLD&gt;
&gt;
&gt; As the door swung open, Nightshift scoots in like a cat trying to get out of
&gt; the house.  He motions Batscout with his tail as he does so, darting in,
&gt; keeping his body low to the ground, padding on silent paws.  Without a sound
&gt; he hides in the darkness of the shadows, and crouches in a corner of the
&gt; room, lying motionless.  He then texts Wolfgang.
&gt;
&gt; &quot;Never mind, I&#39;m in, door just opened, so I took the opportunity when it
&gt; came available.  From here on out, text messages only.  No one knows I&#39;m
&gt; here, except for you guys.  Let&#39;s keep it that way.&quot;

&lt;NEW&gt;

As NIGHTSHIFT went through the door so did BATSCOUT, his movements
nearly soundless, only the small beating of his wings as he came
through the door.

&quot;Will do.&quot; came the text message from both POLAR CLAW and WOLFGANG.

The inside of the next room was pretty large. It was well lit and
dusty. Metal boxes and crates line the wall neatly stacked and totally
undisturbed. If anyone had been in here in a while there was no
evidence of their passage, even the dust on the floor was pristine,
with no footprints or tracks. At the other end of the room there was a
door leading further into the base.

Behind NIGHTSHIFT and BATSCOUT the door they came in began to swing shut.

